ty, or support tools</p><p><strong>Legal Authorities</strong>: If required by law or in case of suspected abuse</p><p><strong>Business Transfers</strong>: In case of a merger or acquisition</p><h3>4. Your Rights &amp; Choices</h3><p>You have the right to:</p><p><strong>Access</strong> your personal data</p><p><strong>Edit or update</strong> your information</p><p><strong>Delete</strong> your account and associated data</p><p><strong>Withdraw consent</strong> to non-essential communications</p><p>To exercise these rights, visit your profile settings or email us at <strong>[support@airwayconnect.com]</strong>.</p><h3>5. Data Retention</h3><p>We retain your data only as long as necessary to:</p><p>Fulfill the purpose it was collected for</p><p>Comply with legal, regulatory, or security obligations</p><p>Allow users to retrieve resumes or application histories</p><p>You can request deletion at any time.</p><h3>6. Security Measures</h3><p>We use industry-standard encryption, firewalls, and secure access protocols to protect your data. However, no system is 100% secure, and we encourage you to use strong passwords and log out after use.</p><h3>7. Cookies &amp; Tracking</h3><p>We use cookies and similar technologies to:</p><p>Keep you logged in</p><p>Remember your preferences</p><p>Analyze site usage for improvement</p><p>You can manage cookie preferences through your browser settings. For more info, refer to our [Cookie Policy].</p><h3>8. Third-Party Links</h3><p>Airway Connect may contain links to third-party websites (e.g., airline companies, job boards). We are not responsible for their privacy practices. We recommend reviewing their privacy policies.</p><h3>9. Children Privacy</h3><p>Airway Connect is not intended for children under 16. We do not knowingly collect personal data from minors. If you believe a minor has registered, please contact us for removal.</p><h3>10. International Users</h3><p>If you access Airway Connect from outside [Insert Country, e.g., India],