            [
                'key'   => 'cookie',
                'value' => '<p>This Cookie Policy explains how <strong>Airway Connect</strong> ("we", "us", or "our") uses cookies and similar technologies to recognize you when you visit our website at <strong>[airwayconnect.com]</strong>. It explains what these technologies are and why we use them, as well as your rights to control our use of them.</p><h3>1. What Are Cookies?</h3><p>Cookies are small text files stored on your device (computer, phone, tablet) when you visit a website. They are widely used to make websites function properly, enhance user experiences, and provide reporting information.</p><p>There are several types of cookies:</p><p><strong>Session Cookies</strong>: Expire when you close your browser</p><p><strong>Persistent Cookies</strong>: Stay on your device for a set period or until deleted</p><p><strong>First-party Cookies</strong>: Set by the website you are visiting</p><p><strong>Third-party Cookies</strong>: Set by services used by the website (e.g., analytics tools)</p><h3>2. How We Use Cookies</h3><p>We use cookies to:</p><p>Keep you logged in and manage your session</p><p>Remember your language and region preferences</p><p>Enable functionality like resume saving or comment replies</p><p>Analyze site performance and traffic (via Google Analytics or similar tools)</p><p>Improve content relevance (e.g., showing jobs based on your activity)</p><p>Prevent abuse and improve security</p><h3>3. Types of Cookies We Use</h3><figure class="table"><table><thead><tr><th>Cookie Type</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Essential</strong></td><td>Necessary for website operation (e.g., login, form submission)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Preferences</strong></td><td>Store user settings and personalization options</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Analytics</strong></td><td>Collect data on user behavior to improve platform (e.g., page views)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Performance</strong></td><td>Measure website speed and feature responsiveness</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Security</strong></td><td>Help detect fraudulent activity or abuse</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Third-Party</strong></td><td>Tools like YouTube, Google Fonts, or embedded job feeds</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p><h3>4. Third-Party Cookies</h3><p>Some third-party services may set their own cookies when you interact with embedded content or external links on Airway Connect. These include:</p><p><strong>Google Analytics</strong></p><p><strong>Cloudflare</strong></p><p><strong>YouTube (if embedded videos are used)</strong></p><p><strong>Job feed integrations (e.g., from airline careers pages)</strong></p><p>We do not control third-party cookies, and their use is governed by their own privacy policies.</p><h3>5. Managing Your Cookie Preferences</h3><p>You can control or delete cookies via your browser settings:</p><p><strong>Chrome</strong>: Settings &gt; Privacy and security &gt; Cookies</p><p><strong>Firefox</strong>: Options &gt; Privacy &amp; Security &gt; Cookies and Site Data</p><p><strong>Safari</strong>: Preferences &gt; Privacy</p><p><strong>Edge</strong>: Settings &gt; Site Permissions &gt; Cookies and site data</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: Disabling cookies may impact the functionality of some features (e.g., staying logged in or saving your resume).</p><p>You may also use third-party tools such as:</p><p>www.aboutads.info/choices</p><p>www.youronlinechoices.eu</p><h3>6. Updates to This Policy</h3><p>We may update this Cookie Policy periodically to reflect changes in cookies we use or for legal, regulatory, or operational reasons.</p><p>You can find the latest version at <strong>[airwayconnect.com/cookie-policy]</strong></p><h3>7. Contact Us</h3><p>If you have any questions about our use of cookies, please contact us at:</p><p>📧 <strong>Email</strong>: [support@airwayconnect.com]</p>',
